<p>I've installed OAuthD (<a href="http://www.evereq.io/evereq/DE" rel="nofollow">http://www.evereq.io/evereq/DE</a>), a background API server,  on a virtual machine running a fresh install of Ubuntu 14.04 x32. I followed these directions listed in the quickstart section of the documentation (<a href="https://github.com/oauth-io/oauthd/wiki/Quickstart" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/oauth-io/oauthd/wiki/Quickstart</a>) and I'm able to successfully create an oauthd instance using 'oauthd init'. But once I enter the directory of the instance and run 'sudo npm install &amp;&amp; sudo grunt', I get the following error:</p>  <pre><code>oauthdgui@oauthdgui-VirtualBox:~/vjf$ sudo npm install &amp;&amp; sudo grunt &gt;&gt; No "coffee" targets found. Warning: Task "coffee" failed. Use --force to continue.  Aborted due to warnings. </code></pre>  <p>The newest version of Grunt is being used, along with the newest version of nodejs and redis. I'm pretty inexperienced with Ubuntu and setting up a server such as this, feel free to make any helpful suggestions. Also I've already tried "--force".</p>  <pre><code>oauthdgui@oauthdgui-VirtualBox:~/vjf$ sudo grunt --force [sudo] password for oauthdgui:  &gt;&gt; No "coffee" targets found. Warning: Task "coffee" failed. Used --force, continuing. &gt;&gt; No "subgrunt" targets found. Warning: Task "subgrunt" failed. Used --force, continuing.  Done, but with warnings. </code></pre>